*********************
*IP Address Tracker *
*********************
project setup, features, and any additiona
******************************************

The IP Address Tracker is a web application that allows users to search for an IP address or domain and view its geographical location on an interactive map.
 The application fetches real-time data from an IP geolocation API and displays details such as IP address, location, timezone, and ISP. 
 The map automatically updates to show the searched location.

Features:
*************
Search for an IP address or domain name
Display IP address information including:
IP Address
Location (City, Region)
Timezone
Internet Service Provider (ISP)
Interactive map showing the location of the IP address
Dynamic map updates when a new IP or domain is searched
Responsive layout for different screen sizes
Technologies Used
React (Frontend framework)
Vite (Build tool)
CSS (Styling)
React Leaflet (Map integration)
IP Geolocation API (Data fetching)

Project Structure
src/
 ├── components/
 │   ├── SearchIPAddress.jsx
 │   ├── InfoCard.jsx
 │   └── MyMap.jsx
 ├── assets/
 │   └── images/
 ├── App.jsx
 ├── main.jsx
 └── index.css

Installation and Setup:
**************************

Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ip-address-tracker.git
Navigate to the project directory
cd ip-address-tracker
Install dependencies
npm install
Start the development server
npm run dev
Open the application in your browser
************************

API Configuration:

This project uses an IP Geolocation API. You need to create an API key and include it in your project.

Example request format:
https://geo.ipify.org/api/v2/country,city?apiKey=YOUR_API_KEY&ipAddress=IP_ADDRESS
For better security, it is recommended to store the API key in an environment variable.
Challenges Faced
Updating the map location dynamically after a new search
Managing component state and passing data between components
Styling the layout to match the provided design
Future Improvements
Add better mobile responsiveness
Implement loading indicators during API requests
Improve error handling for invalid IP addresses
Add animation when the map location updates
